<h2 class="nostyle">Message from the Associate Dean, Research</h2>
Our aim is to provide easy access to the key JMSB faculty operations and the Office of the Associate Dean, Research. Specifically, all issues relating to research, curriculum development, and program appraisals.<br />
<h4>Dr. Lorne Switzer<br />Associate Dean, Research</h4>
-->
<h2>Research</h2>
<p>Our goal is to enhance JMSBâ¬"s research activity for faculty and graduate students and our strategy is regularly updated to reflect the needs of the Faculty.Â  Detailed information about internal and external funding opportunities, awards, guides and forms are available under <a title="Funding Information" href="http://johnmolson.concordia.ca/en/faculty-research/funding-information">Funding Information</a>.<br /><br /><a title="FRC - Faculty Research Committee" href="http://johnmolson.concordia.ca/en/faculty-research/funding-information/faculty-research-committee" target="_blank" id="FRC - Faculty Research Committee">Faculty Research Committee (FRC)</a></p>
<h2>Graduate Research Programs</h2>
JMSB has offered a joint doctoral program since 1976 in affiliation with four other established Montreal business schools. For more information, we invite you to visit the <a title="PhD in Business Administration" href="http://johnmolson.concordia.ca/en/graduate-programs/phd-program">PhD in Business Administration</a> section.<br /><br />The <a title="Master of Science in Administration Program" href="http://johnmolson.concordia.ca/en/graduate-programs/msc-in-admin-program">Master of Science in Administration Program</a> was launched in 1989 as a result of market demand for specialists capable of advanced analytical work, research and consultancy. This program prepares students for specialized managerial and administrative careers in the private and public sectors.</div>
